      </fr:author>
    </fr:authors>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>The Jordan quiver has one vertex and one edge. In this case we have
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ 	V = \{ a \}, \quad  	E = \{ v \}, \quad   ]]></fr:tex>
so there is a unique choice of source and target maps <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s, t \colon  a \longmapsto  v]]></fr:tex>. It is often unnecessary to label the vertices and edges. Then the Jordan quiver is represented as just a dot and a looping arrow.</fr:p>
    <fr:figure>
      <fr:resource hash="90de3da5fc6ef3ec1ecc4499956ce47a">
        <fr:resource-content>
          <fr:img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," />
        </fr:resource-content>
        <fr:resource-source type="latex" part="preamble"><![CDATA[
		\usepackage {tikz}
		\usepackage {tikz-cd}
	]]></fr:resource-source>
        <fr:resource-source type="latex" part="body"><![CDATA[
		\begin {tikzcd}
		\bullet 
		\arrow [loop, distance=2em, in=35, out=325]
		\end {tikzcd}
	]]></fr:resource-source>
      </fr:resource>
    </fr:figure>
  </fr:mainmatter>
